<TITLE> Govt to educate children in risky jobs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com) - - International Labour Organization (ILO) and Economic Relations Department (ERD) have agreed to bring nearly 48,000 children out of their risky jobs and provide them education and training. The agreement was signed by ERD secretary Mosharraf Hossain Bhuiyan and director of ILO Bangladesh Gagan Rajbhandari. The project is supposed to run till Dec 31, 2011. The Netherlands government will provide Tk 706.9 million through ILO. But after signing of the agreement, the ERD secretary told bdnews24.com the timeframe of the project might be extended that as they have got the money late. The labour ministry and the Dhaka City Corporation will implement the project. Several NGOs will work as their associates. Mainly, the children engaged in risky labour in Dhaka city and places around it will be rehabilitated. The Bangladesh government took up the project in 2001 in accordance with an ILO convention regarding risky child labour. The ERD secretary also said they were trying to raise more funds from the development partners. 
